theorem Topology.frontier_eq_compl_of_open_dense {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    IsOpen (A : Set X) → Dense A → frontier (A : Set X) = (Aᶜ : Set X) := by
  intro hOpen hDense
  -- Replace `interior A` and `closure A` using openness and density.
  have hInt : interior (A : Set X) = A := hOpen.interior_eq
  have hCl : closure (A : Set X) = (Set.univ : Set X) := hDense.closure_eq
  -- Unfold `frontier` and simplify.
  calc
    frontier (A : Set X)
        = closure (A : Set X) \ interior (A : Set X) := by
          simp [frontier]
    _ = (Set.univ : Set X) \ (A : Set X) := by
          simpa [hInt, hCl]
    _ = (Aᶜ : Set X) := by
          ext x; simp

theorem Topology.closure_inter_interior_eq_interior {X : Type*}
    [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    closure (A : Set X) ∩ interior A = interior A := by
  ext x
  constructor
  · intro hx
    exact hx.2
  · intro hx
    exact And.intro (subset_closure hx) hx
